widget.name: ListSorter
widget.description: Add a header to your list view or template grid with interactive sorting on click.

property.caption: Header CSS Class
property.description: Zero or more CSS classes to apply to the header label. Uses spaces to separate.

property.caption: List Widget Name
property.description: The name of the list view or template grid to target

property.caption: List Entity
property.description: The type of objects in the list.

property.caption: Default sort
property.description: Whether this widget should enforce sorting on the grid immediately. Only one of the widgets on the page should set the default sort order.

property.caption: Sorting Attribute
property.description: (Optional) The attribute to sort on the grid.

property.caption: Sort Entity (ref)
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The entity containing the attribute to sort.

property.caption: Sort Attribute (ref)
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The attribute to sort on the grid.

property.caption: Sort Entity (refset)
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The entity containing the attribute to sort.

property.caption: Sort Attribute (refset)
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The attribute to sort on the grid.

property.caption: Sec sort order
property.description: Whether the secondary sort should be ascending or descending.

property.caption: Sec Sorting Attribute
property.description: (OPTIONAL) A secondary sort attribute (i.e. sort by Color then Name)

property.caption: Sec Sort Entity
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The entity containing the attribute to sort.

property.caption: Sec Sort Attribute
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The attribute to sort on the grid.

property.caption: Sec Sort Entity (refset)
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The entity containing the attribute to sort.

property.caption: Sec Attribute (refset)
property.description: (OPTIONAL) The attribute to sort on the grid.
